cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

This paper is about semantic video segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new training method that embeds temporal consistency into the segmentation network, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses compact models for real-time execution, which may fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on popular benchmarks, which may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
